	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=71521><span id=Sage>Darniaq</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>40 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>My friend's 42 Beastlord and I (40 Bard) camped the Shadow Men in Lesser Faydark last night. If no one has been there for awhile, there could be a full spawn there. When we arrived, there were SIX mobs, though only Four of them were Shadow Men (the other two were pets).<br><br>We started real carefully, Lull pulling and Charm/Mezzing adds, but eventually realized we could just sit at the spawn point itself :) <br><br>In two solid hours of camping, we walked away with 8 Essences, about 90pp in total and had destroyed uncountable NO RENT weapons. I could have done without the latter, and so could everyone else I could possibly imagine (unless you wanted to the Rapier for Jboots or the Scythe for the Necro Harvester I guess :) )<br><br>The nice thing about this camp is the respawn rate. They don't all respawn at once, and I think the longest we had to wait was about 4 minutes. Most of the time we were lucky to get a 2 minute respite, which was just about right :)<br><br>No XP gains at all, but the fights were challenging when more than two would spawn. Not really deadly, but fun. The things are REALLY fast, as noted numerous places. Not sure I coulda outrun with Selos and Nostrolos, though thankfully didn't need to try :)<br><br>But the pathing is absolutely attrocious, more surprising given it's an outdoor zone. If you stand in front of the ramp at the bottom, a bit aways, and pull from the top, the mob is going to descend the ramp and then run South, East, North, South, West, North, all in a wierd spiral all over the zone EXCEPT where you are. We timed one pull from the ramp (before ascending to camp on it). It took a full 70 seconds for a mob to get from the ramp, through all of Lfay and finally to us. Crazy stuff. Worse than Split Paw and City of Mist on their WORST days :)<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Feb 13 07:37:37 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><span style='color: Red;'>__________________</span style='color: Red;'><br><span style='color: White;'><b>darniaq</b></span style='color: White;'><br><span style='color: Silver;'><span class=sm><b>World of Warcraft</b></span class=sm></span style='color: Silver;'></td></tr>
